        <div type="letter">
            <div type="text">
                <opener>
                    <placeName>[Down.]</placeName>
                    <salute>My dear George.</salute>
                </opener>
                <div type="transcription">
                     
<p>There was heavy rain last night &amp; this morning here, &amp; the walk under the Limes was flooded &amp; water flowed down it. The fruit of Lime-trees formed 12 transverse rows, like a ripple.— You will see by enclosed that each has a little stalk. Would such objects arrange themselves transversely to stream. At the end of each ripple, I think, but dare not say so positively, that the majority of the stalks projected transversely to the line of walk.<ref target="#foot.f2"/></p>
<p>Yours affectionately | C. Darwin</p>
<p>I was dismayed when I first saw them on the walk, for I did not see that each had a stalk.</p> 
                </div>
            </div>
            <div type="tnotes">
                <note xml:id="tnote.n1">1.4 each] <hi rend="italic">after del</hi> ‘the’ </note>
            </div>

        </div>
        
        
